<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenian Foreign Minister Inaugurates Embassy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Foreign Minister Inaugurates Embassy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1206063294 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 12 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1206063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Armenian Foreign Minister Vahan Papazyan arrived in 
Beirut at 2100 yesterday at the head of a Foreign Ministry 
delegation on a four-day official visit to Lebanon. 
  The Armenian foreign minister will inaugurate the Armenian 
Embassy at an opening ceremony in Beirut tomorrow afternoon. 
Minister Papazyan will meet with President Ilyas al-Hirawi, 
Chamber Speaker Nabih Birri, Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, 
Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz, and several ranking officials. 
The talks will deal with the current situation in Lebanon and 
relations between Armenia and Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

