<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Birri Renews Call for Return of General 'Awn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Birri Renews Call for Return of General 'Awn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306125094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 13 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1306125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Christian Usi in the Chamber of Deputies in </F>
Beirut] 
  [Excerpt] Editors Doyen Milhim Karam has cited Chamber of 
Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri as saying that the government will 
be better protected and more prestigious and dignified if it 
lifts all restrictions on the audio and visual media, provided 
that these media are really Lebanese. Birri stressed to the 
editors' doyen that he is one of the advocates of organized 
opposition. He renewed his call for General Michel 'Awn to 
return to Lebanon. If 'Awn needs protection, Birri was quoted 
as saying, I can guarantee him wider and better protection than 
that he is now receiving in his place of residence. Birri 
stressed that General 'Awn was the one who asked for political 
asylum in France, and said Lebanon is prepared to protect him to 
practice all his activities in the country. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

