<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Judge Orders Trial of Ja'ja', Others in Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Judge Orders Trial of Ja'ja', Others in Church Bombing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306084394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0800 GMT 13 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1306084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The judicial official investigating the bombing of 
Sayyidat al-Najat Church in Zuq Mikha'il, Magistrate Joseph 
Furayhah, has issued an indictment against Samir Ja'ja' [leader 
of the dissolved Lebanese Forces Party]; Antonios Ilyas Ilyas, 
alias Tony 'Ubayd; Rushdi Ra'd, alias Nabil Munassa; Jean Yusuf 
Shahin; alias Asad; Jiryis Tawfiq al-Khuri; retired Major Fu'ad 
Malik; Paul al-Fahl; and Rafiq al-Fahl under the criminal code, 
which stipulates certain penalties, including the death penalty. 
  Magistrate Furayhah has referred the entire dossier to the 
Appeals Public Prosecutor, Magistrate Munif 'Uwaydat, for 
further referral to the Judicial Council so that the suspects 
may be tried according to the indictment. 
  Three of the suspects are already in custody; Samir Ja'ja', 
Fu'ad Malik, and Jiryis al-Khuri. Subpoenas in absentia have 
been issued against the others, who are fugitives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

