<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accused Said Linked to Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Accused Said Linked to Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306121094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 13 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1306121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The indictment against Samir 
Ja'ja' and others contains the results of the interrogations of 
the detainees and the information available to the competent 
security and judicial authorities. It reveals that many of the 
accused have received training in Israel and that they had links 
with Israeli intelligence. The interrogations also showed that 
some of them are accomplices in other crimes, such as the 
assassinations of Dani Sham'un and Dr. Ilyas al-Zayik and the 
attempted murder of ministers Elie Hubayqah and Sulayman 
Franjiyah. The indictment points out that the accused possessed 
forged passports and travelled between Cyprus, Juniyah [port in 
Lebanon], and Israel. It also stresses that the accused 
received huge amounts of money for implementing their tasks at 
the direct orders of Ja'ja'. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

