<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   TV Station Ordered to Stop Transmitting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TV Station Ordered to Stop Transmitting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1106195994 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 11 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1106195994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The General Directorate of Public Security decided 
tonight to stop the Future Television station's transmission due 
to violations of the cabinet decision of 23 March 1994, which 
banned the audio and visual media from transmitting direct or 
indirect political news and programs. 
  Future Television transmitted on its news program "Tonight's 
World" a report on the inauguration of the Sidon municipality 
building. The report included the political speech delivered by 
Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, thus violating the cabinet 
decision on the transmission of political news. 
  The public security organ contacted the station and asked it 
to stop transmission. Future Television stopped its 
transmissions at 2030 today [1730 GMT] in obedience to this 
decision. 

</TEXT>

