following conditions should be met: 
  1. The Socialist Party should issue a decision abrogating 
the secession decision. 
  2. It should clearly and frankly announce its acceptance 
of the results of the parliamentary elections held on 27 April 
[1993]. 
  3. It should announce its commitment to the 
constitutional legitimacy and to dealing with the institutions 
accordingly. 
  4. The dialogue should take place in Sanaa. 
  5. The dialogue should not last more than five days. 
  6. The 16 Socialist Party members subpoenaed by the 
public prosecutor should not take part in the dialogue. [end 
recording] 

