<F P=102>   EA1106131394 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1106131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Informed military sources have unmasked the ruling 
military regime in Sanaa by finding out that it has never been 
serious at any time in observing the cease-fire declared by the 
head of the regime following his meeting with Lakhdar Brahimi, 
the special envoy of the UN secretary general. 
  The military sources reported that the northern commander of 
the military axis in Ta'izz had asked the northern units on the 
battlefronts to send a military crew to collect a cable which he 
described as extremely important. The sources confirmed the 
arrival of this cable to the fighting areas at 1730 today. It 
has become clear that the cable contains orders that the war 
operations are to continue and that the cease-fire is to be 
ignored. 
  Meanwhile, the sources have reported that the Popular 
Resistance in the (Amlin) center in al-Dali' Province repulsed 
an infiltration attempt by a gang of the regular forces of the 
military ruling regime in Sanaa two days ago [8th June]. The 
Popular Resistance succeeded in defeating the gang and forced it 
into retreat after destroying two military crews and capturing a 
large lorry carrying military supplies and ammunition belonging 
to the forces of the military regime in Sanaa. Meanwhile, the 
Popular Resistance is gaining strength in the various areas in 
driving out the aggressive invaders. 

</TEXT>

