brother struggler Qa'id 'Ali Muhammad Salah, Central Committee 
member, first secretary of the party's organization in Lahij 
Governorate, who was martyred in front of his home in Dar Sa'd 
on Tuesday [7 June] night as a result of the indiscriminate 
shelling which the al-Amar gangs are launching on the innocent 
citizens and the safe residential areas. [passage omitted] 
  A few days before the death of the martyr Qa'id, his friend 
and comrade, who has the same role and characteristics, the 
brave struggler Naji Muhsin, Central Committee member, first 
secretary of the party's organization in the Ibb Governorate, 
Eastern Region, fell on the same road. 
  At an earlier time and as a result of a treacherous act 
which 
does not befit men, but befits the mercenaries of al-Ahmar gang 
and their agents, the struggler Hanash Thabit Sufyan, member of 
the party's Central Committee member, was martyred. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

