<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Presents Message on Cease-Fire Initiative </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Envoy Presents Message on Cease-Fire Initiative </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1106053194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1106053194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Ambassador 'Abdallah al-Ashtal, our 
country's permanent representative to the United Nations, has 
presented a message to UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali including a new initiative by brother Lieutenant 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential 
Council and supreme commander of the Armed Forces. The message 
states the following: 
  The Republic of Yemen emphasizes its concern to observe a 
cease- fire in accordance with UN Security Council Resolution 
No. 924. This is despite the secessionist rebels' repeated 
flagrant cease- fire violations since 1800 on 9 June--the date 
set by brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Presidential Council chairman and supreme commander of the Armed 
Forces, after his meeting with Lakhdar Brahimi, the UN secretary 
general's envoy. These violations were still continuing up to 
the time this message was drafted. Although the forces of 
legitimacy and unity complied with the the Armed Forces supreme 
commander's order not to respond to those violations, the 
apostate and secessionist elements persisted in their cease-fire 
violations, intensifying their air and naval bombardment of our 
forces in Aden and Abyan governorates, resulting in material and 
human losses among their ranks. Despite all that, the 
Government of the Republic of Yemen has instructed the permanent 
representative to inform the UN secretary general of all those 
violations and to submit a new initiative, on condition that the 
rebels abide by the cease-fire as of midnight last night, 
Friday, 10 June. Out of the Government of the Republic of 
Yemen's concern not to allow the apostate and secessionist 
elements to continue the letting of Yemeni blood within their 
criminal scheme, the brother chairman of the Presidential 
Council has instructed members of the Yemeni military committee, 
which had been set up by a decision by the chairman of the 
Presidential Council and supreme commander of the Armed Forces, 
to supervise the cease-fire by holding its first meeting in a 
specific place named (Ja'ulah), located between Sabir and Dar 
Sa'd villages, at 1100 today, Saturday, 11 June. 

</TEXT>

