<H3> <TI>   Minister Says South Rejected Bid To Stabilize Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Says South Rejected Bid To Stabilize Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1106141994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1330 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1106141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 11 Jun (MENA)--Yemeni Planning Minister Dr. 
'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani has said that what he described as "the 
forces of apostasy and secession" have rejected the new 
initiative by President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih to stabilize the 
cease-fire in Yemen; the proposal would have gone into effect at 
1800 yesterday. In a statement to a MENA correspondent in Sanaa 
he said that the "rebels" are continuing to fight with all types 
of weapons. He stressed that the "the forces of unity and 
legitimacy have completely abided by the cease-fire." He said 
that the "rebels" had refused to attend the Yemeni Military 
Committee meeting in the (Ja'walah) area, between the villages 
of Sabir and Darb al-'Amr near Aden, which had been scheduled 
for 1100 Saturday morning. 

</TEXT>

