<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah has said 
that Yemeni unity is an existent reality that was not imposed by 
force, adding that the separatist elements in the [Yemeni] 
Socialist Party [YSP] leadership are resorting to fighting to 
impose secession by force. He noted that Yemen is one state in 
terms of land and people and that the Yemeni people adhere to 
their unity which is an expression of their will. 
  In a statement to the Qatari radio broadcast yesterday 
evening, Basindwah noted that the secessionist gang violated the 
cease-fire announced by the Yemeni Government before the arrival 
in Sanaa of brother Lakhdar Ibrahimi, envoy of the UN secretary 
general. He added that this gang intensified naval and aerial 
bombardment of the forces of unity and legitimacy to call in 
international observers, something which is unacceptable. He 
said the military confrontation is not between sides, but 
between the legislative government and a gang rebelling against 
legitimacy and seeking secession. 

</TEXT>

