<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Red Cross Aid Ship Stranded off Coast of Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Red Cross Aid Ship Stranded off Coast of Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1206071494 Paris AFP in English 0635 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1206071494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 12 (AFP) -- Aid workers hoped 
Sunday to be able to unload urgently-needed medical supplies for 
Yemen's war wounded from a Red Cross ship stranded off the coast 
of Aden for 24 hours awaiting security guarantees. 
  The Bonsella has been off the port city since Saturday 
trying 
to unload its cargo destined for Yemeni hospitals where stocks 
are rapidly running out, the International Committee of the Red 
Cross (ICRC) said. 
  Sandro Barana, head of the ICRC delegation in Aden, said 
they 
hoped to be able to enter the port on Sunday after obtaining 
guarantees from rival north and south leaders. 
  The Bonsella had tried on June 7 to enter the port but was 
prevented by the fighting. 
  The ICRC has been providing aid to both sides in the Yemen's 
civil war which broke out on May 5 between troops loyal to 
President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his southern rival 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid. 
  Northern Yemeni gunners killed two and wounded 22 in Aden 
late Saturday in the latest round of fighting which has seen 
three ceasefires collapse. 

</TEXT>

