<H3> <TI>   Attacks on Aden Airport, Refinery Resisted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attacks on Aden Airport, Refinery Resisted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1206190194 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1206190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1500 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] An official source in the Democratic Republic of 
Yemen [DRY] has issued the following statement to the Yemeni 
News Agency, Aden: The Sanaa regime has continued to play the 
cease-fire declaration game by first stating the timing of a 
cease-fire and then throwing its forces into a new act of 
aggression by striking at residential quarters and vital 
installations. It then claims the DRY is the one breaking the 
cease-fire. Yesterday the (?collapsing) Sanaa regime said we 
had broken the cease-fire. 
  For the fifth time they declared a cease-fire and then 
ordered their forces to attack on all fronts, while sending 
their aircraft and launching their shells and missiles against 
peaceful residents and vital installations. They made several 
such attacks this morning on the Aden refinery and its civilian 
airport and mounted attacks and shelling on all fronts. Our 
forces and people are heroically resisting and are exhibiting 
legendary steadfastness. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

