<H3> <TI>   Basindwah Returns From Qatari Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Basindwah Returns From Qatari Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1206164194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1600 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1206164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah returned 
to Sanaa this afternoon at the end of a working visit to the 
Qatari capital, Doha. During the visit he delivered a message 
from Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman 
of the Presidential Council, to his brother His Highness Shaykh 
Khalifah Bin-Hamad Al Thani, amir of the State of Qatar, dealing 
with the latest political developments in the Yemeni arena. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', the foreign 
minister expressed his satisfaction with the results of his 
visit to the State of Qatar. 
  He said that during his meetings with the amir of Qatar and 
ranking Qatari officials he conveyed the greetings and 
appreciation of the Yemeni political leadership, led by Brother 
Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential Council 
chairman and commander-in chief of the Armed Forces, for the 
principled and firm pan-Arab positions the State of Qatar on 
various Arab and fateful issues, including the Yemeni crisis. 
  The minister added that he reviewed with the Qatari 
officials 
relations of cooperation between the two sisterly countries and 
issues of bilateral interest. 

