<H3> <TI>   Oil Minister Comments on Return From UK, France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Minister Comments on Return From UK, France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1206174794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1206174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Faysal Bin-'Uthman Bin-Shamlan, minister of 
oil and mineral resources, returned to Sanaa this evening from 
working visits to the United Kingdom and France. The brother 
minister told the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', that he held talks 
during his visit to London with executives of some British 
investment firms, especially those active in the area of oil 
exploration in the Republic of Yemen. These firms, he 
indicated, have shown a readiness to send their experts back to 
resume work as early as this week alongside the local personnel 
who have stayed on their job. Brother Bin-Shamlan added that he 
held similar talks in the French capital, Paris, with officials 
of the Totale [word indistinct] about the exploitation of the 
(Jannah) oilfield in implementation of a Cabinet decision. The 
brother minister said the producing companies, like (Hans) and 
(Sanvienee Ofti) have not halted their operations. 

</TEXT>

