<H3> <TI>   Visit of UN Special Envoy Brahimi Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of UN Special Envoy Brahimi Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Makes Statement, Departs Sanaa </H4>

<F P=102> JN1006110694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1040 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1006110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lakhdar Brahimi, the UN secretary general's 
special envoy, left Sanaa at noon today at the end of a two-day 
visit to our country. During the visit, he met with 
Presidential Council Chairman brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih, government officials, and the leaders of 
political parties and organizations. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni News Agency, SABA', the 
international envoy said he thanks all those he met and who made 
it easy for him to carry out his mission in our country. He 
said his visit was a good beginning. He added: However, we 
aspire for much more. We aspire to see the problem that brought 
us here solved. 
  Brother Lakhdar Brahimi thanked the brother officials of our 
country for their abidance once again by the cease-fire that was 
announced yesterday and which made him optimistic. He said he 
is disappointed because the cease-fire did not hold last night. 

</TEXT>

