<H3> <TI>   Visit of UN Special Envoy Brahimi Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of UN Special Envoy Brahimi Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Visits South for Cease-Fire Talks </H4>

<F P=102> EA1206192794 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1206192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lakhdar Brahimi, the envoy of the UN secretary 
general, arrived in al-Mukalla at 1800 today on his mission to 
establish the facts surrounding the war being fought in Yemen 
and with the objective of bringing about implementation of the 
UN Security Council cease-fire resolution. In a statement to 
the Yemeni News Agency, Aden, he said his presence here was to 
continue talks with the brother officials on the same issues as 
discussed in Sanaa. He went on to say: I believe that the 
sides concerned are those in the north and south of Yemen. What 
we have heard is that they all want a cease-fire, which is what 
we want and want to implement. 
  Brahimi stressed that first and foremost was the 
substantiation of the cease-fire. We shall be talking with the 
brothers about this matter; everything has to be talked about. 
He expressed regret over the violation of the cease-fire, 
saying he hoped it would finally be implemented. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

