<H3> <TI>   Saudi Foreign Minister Visits, Meets With al-Asad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saudi Foreign Minister Visits, Meets With al-Asad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1206111494 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1015 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1206111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1245 today, President Hafiz al-Asad received 
Saudi Foreign Minister Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal. The meeting was 
attended by Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar'. 
  His Highness Prince al-Faysal arrived in Damascus at noon 
today. He was received at Damascus International Airport by 
Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar', a number of Foreign Ministry 
officials, the Saudi ambassador in Damascus, and the Embassy 
staff. 
  In a statement to a SANA correspondent, Prince al-Faysal 
said: I am bringing a message from the custodian of the two 
holy mosques to his brother His Excellency President Hafiz 
al-Asad on two important topics: Bilateral relations and 
continuous consultations on these relations; and the situation 
in our Arab region. 
  Prince al-Faysal added: Within this framework, consultations 
between both countries' leaders are continuous. The custodian 
of the two holy mosques is eager to inform President al-Asad of 
his ideas at all stages. 

