<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-113 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Describes Talks as `Excellent' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Describes Talks as `Excellent' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306085594 Riyadh SPA in Arabic 2215 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 12 Jun -- His Royal Highness Prince Sa'ud 
al-Faysal, the minister of foreign affairs, said that he 
conveyed a message from Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques King 
Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-Aziz to President Hafiz al-Asad of the Syrian 
Arab Republic. 
  His Highness said: "President al-Asad gave me a message in 
reply within the framework of the continuous coordination, 
consultation and assessment of the situation in the region." 
His highness the foreign minister said this in an exclusive 
statement to the Syrian news agency after his meeting with the 
Syrian president today. 
  He described his talks with President Hafiz al-Asad as 
excellent. He stressed the need to end the fighting in Yemen, 
and his highness said that "war cannot be an instrument for 
cooperation between Arab societies." Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal 
expressed the hope that the mission of Lakhdar Brahimi, the UN 
special envoy to Yemen, would be successful, because it proceeds 
from a general international concern to halt the fighting and 
end the current bloody struggle between the two Yemens. 
  His highness stressed that all the disputed issues could be 
settled peacefully on the basis of affection and brotherliness, 
not fighting. He said: "War cannot be an instrument in 
cooperation and cohesion between Arab societies. Proceeding 
from this, we are all concerned with the need to end the 
fighting as soon as possible. I have also noticed this concern 
from our brothers in Syria". 
  His Royal Highness Prince Sa'ud al-Faysal left Damascus this 
evening after a short visit to Syria. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

