<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Continue Implementation of Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Continue Implementation of Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Commander Leaves for Self-Rule Areas </H4>

<F P=102> NC1106145594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1420 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1106145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rafah, 11 Jun (MENA)--Major General 'Abd-al-Raziq 
al-Majayidah, commander of the Palestinian National Security 
Forces, left Rafah today for the self-rule areas at the 
instructions of Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat to acquaint 
himself with the security situation, the deployment of the 
security forces in vital areas and at important installations, 
and to prepare for the arrival in Jericho of 'Arafat and the 
rest of the civilian Authority members. 
  Maj. Gen. al-Majayidah stressed the need for the donor 
nations to provide funds to help the security forces perform 
their duties and establish security and stability in the 
self-rule areas and help the civilian departments to provide 
utilities and infrastructure projects. 
  Economic experts estimate that the civilian authorities will 
need approximately $25 million per month to cover the current 
costs, in addition to the costs of building installations in the 
initial stage of establishing a Palestinian state. 
  Meanwhile, 600 more personnel of the Palestinian National 
Security Forces will arrive in Rafah this evening in preparation 
for entry into the Gaza Strip tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

