<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   DFLP, PFLP Warn of `Dangers' of Jordan-Israel Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DFLP, PFLP Warn of `Dangers' of Jordan-Israel Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1006132394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 10 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1006132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jordan and Israel Tuesday [7 June] signed three 
documents detailing the agenda of negotiations that will lead to 
the signing of a peace treaty. Official sources in Amman said 
the two countries next month will start working out a peace 
agreement after having formed a committee to demarcate their 
joint borders. 
  In a statement to our radio, a spokesman for the unified 
leadership of the Democratic Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine [DFLP] and the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine [PFLP] said the unified leadership of the two fronts 
has warned against the dangers of the Jordanian-Israeli 
agreement and said it opens the door wide for all forms of 
normalization at a time when Israel is still occupying the 
Palestinian and Arab territories, in addition to the fact that 
it is a violation of the principle of a comprehensive solution 
in accordance with international legitimacy, although it is 
hiding behind the first penetration represented by the 
Oslo-Cairo agreement. 
  The central leadership of the two fronts warned against this 
agreement and called on the Jordanian House of Representatives 
and all national Jordanian forces, parties, and personalities to 
reject the agreement and not to allow it to pass on both the 
popular and official levels. The leadership also demanded that 
the Jordanian Government revoke this agreement and abide by the 
principle of comprehensive solution and the constants of the 
pan-Arab position, according to the PFLP and DFLP spokesman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

