<H3> <TI>   Task Forces Formed To Curb Northeastern Insurgencies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Task Forces Formed To Curb Northeastern Insurgencies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1106111294 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 
1630 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1106111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi Doordarshan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Task forces will be constituted beginning today to 
tackle the ongoing insurgency problem in the seven northeastern 
states of the country. This was decided in a meeting between 
Mr. Rajesh Pilot and the chief ministers of Assam, Meghalaya, 
Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim and the governor of 
Manipur in New Delhi this evening. Talking to Doordarshan 
correspondent V. Mira, the minister said that the situation will 
be reviewed after three months with the chief ministers of all 
seven states. 
  [Begin recording] [Mira] How do you view the law and order 
situation in the northeastern states? 
  [Rajesh Pilot] Well, today we had the meeting with all the 
honorable chief ministers of the northeast states. We had 
reviewed the situation. We had reviewed the implementation of 
these decisions and also we took further steps after reviewing 
the situation. What is further needed, we have also decided on 
those lines and I have requested them to go very hard way 
against the insurgents and their activities and what all help 
could be given from center. I have totally offered them that 
center is totally with them to curb the insurgency in 
northeastern region of our country. I feel that Assam, Manipur, 
Nagaland -- these are the three states which are slightly under 
a high pressure of insurgency at the moment. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

