<F P=103> LD1006183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 10, IRNA -- Bosnian Minister of Foreign 
Affairs Irfan Ljubljankic in a speech at the Friday prayers here 
today thanked Iranian Muslim people for their aid to his people. 
  "Iranian relief aid stregthened this feeling in the Bosnian 
people that they are not alone in their legitimate defence 
against aggressors," he said. 
  Up to now, he said, over 200,000 Bosnian Muslims have been 
killed and that the only reason for the whole aggression and 
massacre of innocent people is that the Bosnian people were 
Muslim. 
  He termed the defence against the Serbian aggression as "the 
natural right of the Bosnian people" and called for the lifting 
of the arms embargo on his country. 
  Ljubljankic who arrived here today for talks with the 
Iranian 
authorities on the current Bosnian peace negotiations, said that 
the Bosnian Government would continue its efforts to gain the 
United Nations consent to the dispatch of the Islamic for 
[passage indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

