<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy: Iran To Help Rebuild Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Envoy: Iran To Help Rebuild Sarajevo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806194894 Tehran IRNA in English 1630 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 8, IRNA -- The Vienna conference has 
decided to include Iran in the coordination group set up for the 
reconstruction of Sarajevo, envoy of the U.N. secretary-general, 
William Eagleton announced here Wednesday. 
  Eagleton in a meeting with Deputy Foreign Minister for 
International Affairs Mohammad Javad Zarif also presented the 
documents of various projects for reconstruction of Sarajevo, 
and explained the projects's priorities. 
  Zarif in return emphasized the importance of supporting the 
reconstruction projects in Sarajevo and said Iran was ready to 
have active presence in them. 
  The conference on the reconstruction of Sarajevo was held in 
Vienna on 24-25 May at the invitation of the U.N. secretary 
general envoy to the former Yugoslavia. 
  Senior officials of the Bosnian Government and 
representatives from 30 countries including Iran participated in 
the conference. 

</TEXT>

