<H3> <TI>   Velayati's Visit to Germany Previewed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Velayati's Visit to Germany Previewed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006163094 Tehran IRNA in English 1459 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 10, IRNA -- Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati will leave here for Germany on Monday [13 June] to 
follow up the issues raised in the previous telephone 
conversations between President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani and 
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, announced a Foreign Ministry 
spokesman here today. 
  The spokesman, Mahmud Mohammadi, said during the visit 
Velayati would also hand over a message from President 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani to Chancellor Kohl. 
  While in Bonn, Velayati is also to discuss expansion of 
bilateral ties as well as Iran's relations with the European 
Union (EU) with other German authorities. 
  Political observers attach importance to the Velayati's 
visit 
to Germany in the wake of the Germany's EU presidency in July. 

</TEXT>

