<H3> <TI>   Va'ezi Gives Message From President to Mitterrand </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Va'ezi Gives Message From President to Mitterrand </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1106063794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1106063794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani's written message was 
handed over to President Francois Mitterrand in Paris by Va'ezi, 
the deputy foreign minister for Euro-American affairs. 
  According to the Central News Unit, during this meeting the 
French president stressed the importance of Iran in the region 
and described the broadening of Tehran-Paris relations. He 
said: Fortunately, the problems that existed in the path of the 
expansion of relations between the two countries are in the 
process of being eliminated. 
  Francois Mitterrand added: France is seeking durable and 
reliable relations with Iran and the two sides should work 
toward this end. He expressed his pleasure at the message from 
President Hashemi-Rafsanjani and called for more frequent 
contacts between the officials of the two countries. 
  During this meeting, Va'ezi declared the Islamic Republic of 
Iran's readiness to broaden relations with France in all fields. 

</TEXT>

