<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abu-Nidal Group Member Claims Lockerbie Responsibility </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abu-Nidal Group Member Claims Lockerbie Responsibility </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306105594 Paris AFP in English 1048 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1306105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, June 13 (AFP) -- A member of Abu Nidal's 
radical Palestinian group Fatah Revolutionary Council claimed 
here on Monday responsibility for bombing a US airliner over 
Lockerbie, Scotland, in December 1988, which killed 270 people. 
  Yusuf Sha'ban, 29, a suspect in the murder case of a 
Jordanian diplomat, told a Lebanese court he had placed the bomb 
that ripped through a Pan Am plane packed with Christmas 
travellers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

