<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Hariri Rejects Separate Peace With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Hariri Rejects Separate Peace With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1106161194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 11 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1106161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri emphasized in Sidon 
this afternoon that the continuing Israeli aggression against 
Lebanon's territory, sovereignty, and dignity, whether involving 
villages, individuals, or groups, will not force Lebanon to 
conclude a separate peace deal with Israel or even to discuss 
it. They will not succeed in putting on a collision course the 
logic of the state and the logic of the honest, rational, and 
objective resistance, which complements the work of the state 
for liberation by its steadfastness, he added. 
  The prime minister added that we will not give Israel the 
satisfaction of seeing any crack in the unity of the Lebanese, 
who on the contrary are tending toward more strength, cohesion, 
and firmness. Prime Minister al-Hariri reiterated that Lebanon 
joined the negotiations in collaboration and consultation with 
Syria and with a well-known objective--namely, to liberate every 
inch in the south, the Western al-Biqa', and the Golan. 
  Prime Minister al-Hariri made these remarks after 
inaugurating the municipality offices in Sidon. 

</TEXT>

