<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Kuwait </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Receives First War Reparations Payment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Receives First War Reparations Payment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206153494 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 1313 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1206153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kuwait, 12 Jun -- Finance and Planning Minister 
Nasir 'Abdallah al-Rawdan announced today that the Ministry of 
Finance had received $1.397 million from the UN Reparation 
Committee. The money is the first installment for victims of 
Iraqi aggression and is in compensation for physical and 
psychological damages under the terms of damages/group B as 
defined by the Geneva-based agency. 
  Al-Rawdan told KUNA that the Ministry of Finance, in 
coordination with the public commission in charge of estimating 
losses resulting from the Iraqi aggression, would determine 
payment procedures to those who deserve them. [passage omitted] 
  The first installment sum is $2.74 million dollars [as 
received] which will be disbursed among 670 victims of the Iraqi 
invasion. They are victims as defined under group B terms, 
which includes cases of death and serious injuries. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

