<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden Accuses Sanaa of Violating Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Accuses Sanaa of Violating Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1106130094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 2045 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1106130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 2045 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Presidential Council in 
the Democratic Republic of Yemen made the following statement to 
the Yemeni News Agency, Aden: 
  We have heard about a so-called initiative from 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih presented by his envoy al-Ashtal [as heard] to 
the United Nations which stipulates for a cease-fire as from 
midnight this evening, and commissions what he called a Joint 
Military Committee, formed during the union period which has 
been blown up by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, to examine the situation. 
  We would like to illustrate clearly the position of the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen in the following manner: 
  First, 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his forces were those who 
started the aggression on the Democratic Republic of Yemen's 
forces and territories. 
  Second, 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his regime have rejected 
all 
Arab and international initiatives. 
  Third, the Security Council has issued its resolution No. 
924 
and we had sincerely announced our adherence to it immediately 
after it was announced, but 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his regime 
clearly refused to abide by this resolution until yesterday when 
he announced his adherence to its text and spirit and specified 
3 o'clock in the evening for the start of implementing the 
ceasefire, though the resolution has stipulated for adherence to 
it and though 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih has previously announced two 
cease-fires which he violated. 
  Fourth, for the third time 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his 
forces violated the ceasefire last night. The whole world knows 
that it was he who violated the cease-fire half-an-hour after 
the time he committed himself to cease the firing. 
  Fifth, we shall continue to adhere to the rulings of the 
Security Council's Resolution No. 924 without preconditions, and 
will only defend ourselves against any violation or aggression 
by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his forces. 
  Sixth, the Joint Military Committee or a Yemeni military 
committee, which 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih claims to have set up 
perviously, do not exist any more. International observers, not 
imaginary committees formed by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, should 
monitor the cease-fire. 
  This the position of the Democratic Republic of Yemen which 
it adheres to and announces to the international community. 

</TEXT>

