  [Text] Egypt has voiced concern over the repeated 
noncompliance with a cease-fire in Yemen, warning that a 
cease-fire should take priority over any other consideration. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Counselor Nazi al-Khudayr made a 
statement to our radio correspondent commenting on the 
unsuccessful attempts to maintain a cease-fire in Yemen. He 
said: Egypt backs any efforts to resolve the disputes among the 
brothers in Yemen in a peaceful manner that will preserve the 
country's remaining resources and the mutual trust among its 
sons. 

