<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Arrest 47 `Terrorists,' Seize Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Arrest 47 `Terrorists,' Seize Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1006212394 Cairo AL-AHRAM in Arabic 9 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC1006212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-AHRAM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Interior Ministry's security agencies have 
arrested 47 terrorists of a military wing linked with the 
deceased terrorist Tal'at Yasin Hammam. Thus, the number of 
suspects from the so- called al-Jama'ah al-Islamiyah [the 
Islamic group] has risen to 145 terrorists, who represent the 
basic echelon from which terrorists are assigned tasks in 
assassinations and explosions in greater Cairo and the Upper 
Egypt governorates. 
  The State Security Detective Agency conducted a series of 
significant security operations, storming terrorist hideouts in 
the governorates over the past days. 
  This group, whose members had participated in numerous 
terrorist attacks, primarily the assassination of the secretary 
of the State Security Detective Agency, Major General Ra'uf 
Khayrat, was tracked down in complete secrecy. All the suspects 
were arrested alive and the security authorities obtained 
important confessions from them on the circumstances of the 
crime and the monitoring and financing operations for which 
terrorist Tal'at Hammam and many of his partners, both in and 
outside the country, were responsible. 
  At the hideouts they raided in the governorates, which 
number 
more than 20, the authorities found automatic rifles, pistols, 
explosive charges, and other equipment, plus many organizational 
documents indicating foreign funding sources and the 
organization's planned targets. About half a million pounds and 
$80,000 were seized in the operation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

