<H3> <TI>   Paper Assails Israeli Actions, Rabin's Statements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Assails Israeli Actions, Rabin's Statements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306141494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0605 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Jun (MENA)--The newspaper AL-AKHBAR has 
expressed astonishment over Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin's abandonment of his previous approval of the issue of 
peace in the Middle East, especially with respect to 
negotiations with Syria. 
  In a comment published today, the newspaper noted that Rabin 
announced he had never said anything about Israel's readiness to 
withdraw from all the territories of the Syrian Golan Heights if 
Damascus agrees to reach a comprehensive peace with the Jewish 
state. During the negotiation rounds in Washington, Rabin 
repeated this promise over and over again. 
  The newspaper adds that on the Israeli-Palestinian track, 
Rabin has also issued threats and warnings, sometimes convincing 
and at other times flagrant, even after implementation of the 
first stage of the autonomy agreement between the PLO and Israel 
started. 
  The newspaper explained that as regards Lebanon, the 
Security 
Council issued Resolution 425, which stipulated the need for the 
Israeli forces to withdraw from southern Lebanon. In addition, 
despite the fact that negotiations between the two sides started 
in Washington and officially still exist, Israeli attacks on 
Lebanon continue. In fact, they have reached the stage where 
Israeli commandos kidnapped a southern Lebanese leader from his 
home publicly and with eyewitnesses to testify. 
  Concluding its comment, AL-AKHBAR stated that the Israeli 
practices confirm that all Israel's claims and promises 
regarding peace with the Arabs are nothing more than illusions 
and whims. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

