<H3> <TI>   Israelis Banned From Jericho Until Further Notice </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israelis Banned From Jericho Until Further Notice </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1006114494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 10 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1006114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Since last night, Israelis have been banned from 
entering the Jericho autonomy region until a new announcement is 
issued. Our correspondent Ron Nesi'el reports that the reason is 
concern about attempts to attack Israelis after hundreds of 
Palestinian prisoners arrived in the town. Jericho itself is 
quiet. There is a large Palestinian police presence, especially 
in the area of the mosque, but there have been no reports of 
disturbances. 

</TEXT>

