<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Justice Minister Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemeni Justice Minister Arrives on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With King Husayn </H4>

<F P=102> JN1106160894 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 
10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1106160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, in the presence of His Royal Highness 
Crown Prince Hasan, His Majesty King Husayn received 'Abdallah 
Ahmad Ghanim, the Yemeni minister of justice, who conveyed to 
his majesty an oral message from President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Yemeni Presidential Council. The message deals 
with the latest developments in the Yemeni Republic, expressing 
appreciation for Jordan's pan-Arab stand and its concern for 
Yemen's unity and achievements. 
  His Majesty King Husayn stressed Jordan's support for 
fraternal Yemen's unity and democracy. 
  The meeting was attended by His Highness Prince 'Abdallah 
Bin- Husayn; Dr.'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, the prime minister; 
al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, the chief of the Royal Hashemite 
Court; and the Yemeni ambassador to Jordan. 

</TEXT>

