<F P=106> ["Text" of cable from from Saudi King Fahd </F>
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, custodian of the two holy mosques, to King 
Husayn; date not given -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] Your Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal, king of the 
Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan: I have received your majesty's 
cable on the occasion of the advent of the Islamic New Year. I 
am pleased to exchange congratulations with you on this dear 
occasion, wishing that this occasion will return while your 
majesty enjoyed good health, while the fraternal Jordanian 
people enjoyed prosperity under your wise leadership, and while 
our Arab and Islamic nation realized their noble hopes and 
goals. Peace and God's mercy and blesses be upon you. 
  [Signed] Your brother Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud, 
custodian of the two holy mosques and king of the Kingdom of 
Saudi Arabia 

