<H3> <TI>   Participation at Tel Aviv Tourism Conference Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Participation at Tel Aviv Tourism Conference Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1206191894 Paris AFP in English 1741 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1206191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman, June 12 (AFP) -- Jordan's tourism association 
on Sunday denied an Israeli newspaper report that five 
Jordanians were to attend a conference in Tel Aviv. 
  "No member of the association, which represents the whole of 
the private sector, is going to take part" in the tourism 
conference opening on Monday, its director Yusuf Muwaswas told 
AFP. 
  Tourism Minister Muhammad 'Adwan also denied the report, 
saying his ministry had not been informed of any such 
participation. 
  The Israeli daily HA'ARETZ reported earlier that five 
Jordanians were to attend the conference for travel agents. 
  Israel and Jordan resumed peace negotiations last week and 
signed agendas for treaty talks covering water, energy, 
environment, security and territorial issues. 

</TEXT>

