<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Arrives in Geneva, Greeted by Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Arrives in Geneva, Greeted by Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306173694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1542 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1306173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, 13 Jun (MENA)--President Mubarak arrived in 
Geneva tonight. He was welcomed at the airport by senior 
officials of the Geneva canton; heads of the permanent missions 
to the United Nations; Dr. Mahir Mahran, state minister for 
population and family affairs; Mahir al-Sadiq, Egyptian 
ambassador to Bern; and Munir Zahran, head of Egypt's permanent 
delegation to the United Nations in Geneva. 
  Accompanying President Mubarak on his trip are Information 
Minister Safwat al-Sharif and Dr. Zakariya 'Azmi, director of 
the Presidential Office. 

</TEXT>

