<H3> <TI>   Radio Cites UK Paper on Saddam's Health </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Cites UK Paper on Saddam's Health </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1006153094 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1006153094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The British DAILY EXPRESS newspaper on Wednesday 2 
June 1994 reported that tyrant Saddam has been undergoing 
extensive medical observation for some time due to his serious 
heart condition. The newspaper said that recently he has been 
frequently slipping into a coma because of the weak blood flow 
from his heart to his brain. The paper noted that the Baghdad 
tyrant has not made any public appearances due to his critical 
medical condition. 

</TEXT>

