<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kurdish Organizations Sign Cease-Fire Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kurdish Organizations Sign Cease-Fire Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1006211294 (Clandestine) Kurdistan Voice of Unification in 
Arabic 1700 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1006211294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Kurdistan Voice of Unification </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The operations room in the al-Sulaymaniyah 
Governorate has started its work. It met in the area under the 
control of the Kurdistan Democratic Party [KDP] and the Islamic 
Movement. It is noteworthy that most of the areas north and 
east of al-Sulaymaniyah Governorate are under the control of the 
peshmerga and mujahidin of our KDP and the Islamic Movement. 
  The operations room held its first meeting in (Girdanata), 
situated a few kilometers east of Sayyid Sadiq. The following 
decisions were made: 
  A comprehensive cease-fire; the formation of a subcommittee 
for operations from representatives of the INC [Iraqi National 
Congress] and the three parties--the KDP, the Patriotic Union of 
Kurdistan [PUK], and the Islamic Movement. 
  Decision: The operations room decided the following at its 
meeting in the village of (Girdanata): 
  1. The PUK should withdraw its forces from the villages of 
Gamish Tappah and Nawgirdan. The INC forces will be stationed 
there. The KDP and the Islamic Movement forces shall not enter 
the two villages. 
  2. The INC will control the village of (Girdanata) and act 
as an observation post for the signatories. 
  The decision was signed by Brigadier General Talal 
al-'Ubaydi 
for the INC, Jawhar Namiq for the KDP, Mulazim 'Umar 'Abdallah 
for the PUK, and Kamil 'Ali for the Islamic Movement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

