<H3> <TI>   Ramadan Calls For Disease Prevention Efforts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramadan Calls For Disease Prevention Efforts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0706085094 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1800 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0706085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Taha Yasin Ramadan, Revolution Command Council 
member and vice president, has called for spreading health 
awareness among citizens and enhancing ways to prevent disease 
through domestic educational programs and popular seminars in 
the cities and villages of our great Iraq in order to prevent 
illnesses before treating them. 
  During a meeting with the head and members of the Iraqi Red 
Crescent Society, Ramadan described the suffering of the sons of 
our people, particularly the children and elderly, due to the 
blockade and resulting shortage of medicines as the crime of the 
age, a violation of human rights, and an encroachment on divine 
values and international charters. 
  The vice president added that the continued food and 
medicine 
blockade on the Iraqi people has exposed both the enemies of 
mankind and those who are using the defense of human rights, 
peoples' freedom, and peoples' prosperity, as a disguise. He 
noted the importance of moves by charitable and humanitarian 
organizations to reject the U.S.-led hostile policy which is 
implemented by the U.S. allies who are fighting the Iraqi people 
using food and medicines after they failed to harm them through 
a wide military aggression. 
  Dr. Sa'dun Khalifah, head of the Society, reviewed its 
efforts to alleviate the illnesses which the children and 
elderly are suffering as a result of the continued blockade. 

</TEXT>

