<F P=102>   JN0506113594 Baghdad INA in English 0820 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0506113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, June 5, INA--Baghdad's Chamber of Commerce 
has recently received commercial offers from a number of Arab 
and foreign companies for economic and commercial cooperation 
with Iraq. 
  In a statement to a local daily, chairman of the Baghdad's 
Chamber of Commerce Zuhayr 'Abd-al-Ghafur said the chamber has 
received an offer from a British firm specialised in food 
processing and another offer from an Australian firm specialized 
in exporting wheat, rice, sugar, milk and meat. 
  Moreover, the chamber has also received an offer from the 
Egyptian al-Zahra' Company for Construction Materials, Steel and 
Glass, said Mr. 'Abd-al-Ghafur, adding that seven other 
companies from Spain, Pakistan, India, Turkey, Jordan, Singapore 
and Sri Lanka have expressed their desire and readiness to 
resume and establish commercial ties with Iraqi traders. 

</TEXT>

