<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP `Gang' Said To Bar Food Convoy From Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP `Gang' Said To Bar Food Convoy From Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1306092294 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0800 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1306092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The gang of apostasy and secession in the [Yemeni] 
Socialist Party [YSP] leadership has prevented a food convoy 
from entering Aden. Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council and supreme 
commander of the Armed Forces, instructed the Government to 
prepare this convoy within 24 hours, send it to Aden, and 
distribute it free of charge among the residents of Aden, the 
economic and commercial capital. 
  Deputy Prime Minister brother Dr. 'Abd-al-Qadir Ba Jammal 
explained that in implementation of the instructions of the 
brother chairman leader, the Government prepared a convoy of 100 
trailers, 40 carrying wheat, 30 carrying rice, 21 carrying 
various products including peas, broad beans, vegetable oil, 
ghee, and tomato paste, and nine trailers carrying various kinds 
of vegetables. 
  Ba Jammal said that the Government informed the 
International 
Red Cross that it is preparing this food convoy as part of a 
plan for the free distribution of these products among the Aden 
residents in accordance with the UN plans and programs. 
  At a news conference he held in Sanaa yesterday afternoon, 
Ba 
Jammal said that the Government yesterday received a message 
from the Red Crescent and the Red Cross through their regional 
representatives in the Arabian Peninsula stating they had met 
with other officials and that the matter needs the approval of 
the other party, which, unfortunately, views this humanitarian 
gesture as a political action. He said that this is the story 
behind the obstruction of our humanitarian initiative by those 
who remained outside the homeland for 25 years and now returned 
to speak on behalf of its sons and prevent this assistance from 
reaching the sons of heroic Aden. 
  At the news conference attended by correspondents from the 
local, Arab, and international media in Sanaa, the brother 
deputy prime minister denied the allegations and falsehoods 
circulated by the trumpets of the gang of apostasy and secession 
to the effect that the aircraft of the forces of unity and 
constitutional legitimacy are launching raids on the Aden 
refinery. He said the forces of unity and constitutional 
legitimacy are careful not to harm this refinery or other vital 
economic installations. 
  Brother Ba Jammal said that contacts continue with the 
unionist leaders in the YSP, both in and outside Yemen. He 
explained that these contacts take place through national 
figures from other groupings. 
  The deputy prime minister, replying to questions posed by 
the 
media correspondents, tackled the national issues pertaining to 
the current developments in the Yemeni arena. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

