<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ahmad Birru from Sanaa] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Informed sources in Sanaa have 
announced that Saudi troops are being massed near the common 
border [with Yemen]. The sources noted that more than 150 Saudi 
tanks have been moved toward the border, near the Yemeni 
district of Maydi, adding that these tanks have taken up combat 
positions. 
  The sources said Sanaa has officially asked the United 
States, Britain, and France, which have satellites, to verify 
these moves. 
  No official sources have confirmed or denied this 
information 
which has not reported by independent sources. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

