<H3> <TI>   Aden Establishes Defense Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Establishes Defense Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1306212794 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1800 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1306212794 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1800 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, chairman of the 
Presidential Council, today issued Republican Decree No. 10 of 
1994 concerning the setting up of the National Defense Council. 
  Article 1 of the decree provides for the formation of the 
National Defense Council as follows: 
  The chairman of the Presidential Council will act as 
chairman. Other members include deputy chairman and members of 
the Presidential Council, speaker of the National Assembly, 
prime minister, foreign minister, minister of defense, interior 
and security minister, finance minister, minister of culture and 
information, chief of the general staff, and, acting as 
rapporteur, the adviser to the Presidential Council on military 
affairs. 
  Article 2 of the decree states that it is effective from the 
date of its issuance and that it shall be published in the 
official gazette. 

</TEXT>

