<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Said To Convey Israeli Ultimatum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Said To Convey Israeli Ultimatum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1306153694 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 11 Jun 94 pp 1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1306153694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Washington Conveyed Israeli </F>
Ultimatum to Lebanon"] 
  [Text] Beirut, AL-HAYAH -- Official Lebanese sources have 
told AL-HAYAH that, some days ago, the United States conveyed to 
Lebanon an Israeli ultimatum that Israel would hit Lebanon hard 
if Hizballah retaliated to its bombing of Hizballah's bases and 
centers with suicide operations abroad or across the Lebanese 
borders. 
  The sources said that U.S. Ambassador in Beirut Mark Hambley 
conveyed that ultimatum to the senior Lebanese officials he met 
with in the past few days, pointing out that Israel's ultimatum 
was in reply to Hizballah leaders' declarations that they would 
retaliate to the Israeli raid on 'Ayn Kawkab camp near Ba'labakk 
last week with suicide operations inside [Israel] and abroad. 
The raid left 35-40 Hizballah members dead, of whom 27 have been 
named, and 70 others injured. 
  The ultimatum, as conveyed by the American side, was that no 
Hizballah position in Lebanon would be safe, and it held the 
Lebanese Government responsible. 
  The sources told AL-HAYAH that the ultimatum was repeated by 
Uri Lubrani, head of the Israeli delegation to the negotiations 
with Lebanon, in statements he made the day before yesterday 
threatening a relentless war if Lebanon continued to embrace 
Hizballah. Senior Lebanese officials said they feared a major 
Israeli operation in the coming days as a consequence of that 
ultimatum and Lubrani's warnings. They have been concerned, 
particularly as the Western states and the United States clearly 
opposed their desire to have the Security Council issue a 
statement condemning Israel's violation of Lebanese sovereignty 
when it launched these raids last week. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-36824 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes114_n_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-114 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

