<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Hirawi Receives Yemeni Justice Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1306175094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 13 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1306175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ilyas al-Hirawi received Yemeni Justice 
Minister 'Abdallah Ahmad Ghanim at the B'abda Palace this 
evening. Yemeni Ambassador to Lebanon Ahmad Muhammad 
al-Mutawakkil also attended. After the meeting, the Yemeni 
minister said that he delivered a verbal message to President 
al-Hirawi from Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih regarding 
the latest developments of the war in Yemen. He said the war 
was ignited by the separatists to break up Yemen and to move the 
country backward. He added: I was pleased by his excellency 
the president's response and eagerness for Yemen's stability, 
security, and continued unity. The Yemeni minister arrived in 
Beirut earlier today. 

</TEXT>

