<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Velayati Departs for Bonn Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Velayati Departs for Bonn Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306082794 Tehran IRNA in English 0812 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 13, IRNA -- Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati left here for Bonn Monday at the official invitation of 
his German counterpart Klaus Kinkel to discuss mutual ties and 
key regional and international issues. During his two-day 
visit, Velayati will discuss Iran's ties with the European Union 
in his meetings with Chancellor Helmut Kohl, Foreign Minister 
Kinkel and other German officials. 
  Political observers attach great importance to Velayati's 
visit with regard to the fact that Germany will take over the 
rotating chairmanship of the European Union next month. 

</TEXT>

