<H3> <TI>   President Says Economy in Better Shape </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Says Economy in Better Shape </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106174294 Tehran IRNA in English 1713 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 11, IRNA -- President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani in his inaugural address to the Second 
Congress of Construction Jihad here today said the country was 
on the road to progress and despite the existing bottlenecks the 
economic situation was in "complete natural gear." 
  He said Iran possesses machineries, industrial raw materials 
and energy sources, which fact should make the path of the 
second 5-year development smoother. 
  The Iranian economy was in a better position today than five 
years ago, he added. 
  On the fuel problem in the country, Hashemi-Rafsanjani said 
Iran would face no problem in this connection since its natural 
gas production of 120 to 130 million cubic meters per day 
exceeds its domestic demand of only 80 million cubic meters. 
  He appreciated the efforts of construction jihad workers and 
reiterated the importance of training and research for the 
country's reconstruction. 

</TEXT>

