<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i Urges Muslims Not To Sell Oil to West </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamene'i Urges Muslims Not To Sell Oil to West </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106152494 Tehran IRNA in English 1428 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 11, IRNA -- Leader of Islamic 
revolution Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i blamed those oil-producing 
states who supported hegemonic powers rather than defending the 
rights of their own countries and nations causing sharp fall in 
oil prices. 
  Ayatollah Khamene'i made the remark in the oil-rich city of 
Gachsaran Friday morning on the last day of his four-day tour of 
Kohkiloyeh-Boyer Ahmad Province in southwestern Iran. 
  The leader also said that Iran was the only member of the 
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) to 
annnounce its stance and seriously insist on it. 
  Ayatollah Khamene'i said that the progress of arrogant 
Europe 
and America is based on oil which belongs to the Middle East, 
Persian Gulf and other Muslim regions. If the Muslims stop the 
export of their oil to the West, the industrial societies would 
be reduced to lifeless shells, he added. 
  Ayatollah Khamene'i further noted that due to the treachery 
of some of the regional allies of Europe and America, oil --the 
backbone of industiral civilzaiton-- is sold at a very low price 
so much so that the West's profit from oil imports and taxes is 
much higher than what the producing countries gain through oil 
exports. 
  Leader of the Islamic revolution said that the awakening of 
the Muslim nations was the only remedy to the problems of the 
Muslim world. 

</TEXT>

