<H3> <TI>   Preparations Under Way for 'Arafat Return to Jericho </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Preparations Under Way for 'Arafat Return to Jericho </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Personnel Arrive in Gaza </H4>

<F P=102> JN1306193194 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 13 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1306193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Reports received from the Palestinian territories 
today say about 270 Palestinian policemen and employees arrived 
in the autonomous Gaza Strip last night. This group, which 
arrived from Tunis and Cairo, is scheduled to prepare for 
brother President Abu-'Ammar's [Yasir 'Arafat] arrival in 
Jericho and the Gaza Strip, expected late this month. 

</TEXT>

