<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Said To Dismiss Intelligence Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Said To Dismiss Intelligence Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1406093894 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 13 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> JN1406093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] AL-MAJD has learned that President Saddam Husayn 
has made major changes in the Iraqi security agencies. Major 
General Sabir al-Duri, director of the General Intelligence, was 
transferred to the post of an adviser at the Presidency and 
replaced as director of General Intelligence by al-Anbar 
Governor Mani' 'Abd-al-Rashid. 
  A reliable source arriving from Iraq said three more 
officials from the al-Duri tribe, which is known for its close 
links to the regime, were dismissed from their posts. These are 
Khadr al-Duri, member of the Regional Command of the ruling 
Ba'th Party; 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Duri; and 'Abd-al-'Aziz al-Duri, 
who is said to have fled to Syria. 
  The Iraqi source said Maj. Gen. al-Duri was dismissed from 
his post as intelligence chief probably after it was discovered 
that the Iraqi intelligence service was involved in the 
assassination of the Iraqi opposition figure Shaykh Talib Suhayl 
in Beirut and the assassination of a German journalist named 
Lisi Schmidt [name as published]. An officer named Safi 
al-Tikriti was in charge of the two operations. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

