<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decisions Made on Tackling Economic Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Decisions Made on Tackling Economic Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406211994 Tripoli Libyan Television Network in Arabic 
1930 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Libyan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Secretariat of the General People's 
Committee concluded today its 10th ordinary meeting for this 
year. 
  Following its two-day meeting, the committee adopted a 
number 
of decisions on facing up to some negative phenomena which have 
caused an increase in the prices of a number of commodities and 
services, and to the causes of the pressures on the Libyan dinar 
-- pressures brought about by certain unlawful practices -- 
which have led to a drop in the real value of the income of part 
of the population. 
  The committee's Secretariat has asked the Central Bank of 
Libya to study the matter and come up with a date to start 
paying sums of money in hard currency to citizens to enable them 
to face up to their difficulties, as well as to define what sums 
of money should be paid in every deserving case. 
  The Secretariat has reiterated the need to the brother 
secretary of the General People's Committee for economy and 
trade and to the governor of the Central Bank of Libya to open 
the credits necessary for the provision of the local market with 
the required commodities, through the legally recognized 
channels. [passage omitted] 
  The Secretariat has also asked the Central Bank of Libya to 
consider an increase in the interest rate in order to encourage 
savings with the banks. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

