<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, 12 Jun (JANA) -- The Western official mass 
media has launched a noticeable campaign, characterized by panic 
and alarm, against the statements made to a Lebanese court by 
Palestinian defendant Yusuf Sah'ban. The campaign has been 
started in an attempt to cast doubt over these statements. The 
Palestinian defendant has admitted to the whole world that he 
blew up Pan Am flight 103 over Lockerbie in Scotland. 
  JANA's international affairs editor comments on this by 
querying the reasoning behind the panic among the western mass 
media and colonialist quarters. He wonders about the reason 
behind this unprecedented uproar, which began when the 
Palestinian defendant announced his admission -- which was heard 
by the whole world with no exception. 
  Does this panic express a breakdown in the plots of 
colonialism and material forces? This expresses their bitter 
feeling that they have failed once again, and in an undisputed 
way, to defend their fabrications, mask their lies, and to turn 
them into realities. 

</TEXT>

