<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mubarak Accepts UN Award, Meets Swiss President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1406190794 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1406190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] President Muhammad Husni Mubarak today received 
the UN population award at a special ceremony held at the UN 
Headquarters in Geneva. The award is in recognition of 
Mubarak's pioneering role in resolving the population problem 
since he took office. UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali handed Mubarak the award. President Mubarak 
acknowledged it with a speech stating the need to resolve the 
problem of overpopulation in developing countries. [passage 
omitted] 
  President Mubarak met Otto Stich, president of the Swiss 
Confederation, at the offices of the Swiss delegation to the 
United Nation at noon today. According to Information Minister 
Safwat al- Sharif, the two leaders exchanged views on a number 
of international and regional issues, particularly the Middle 
East. President Mubarak and Stich discussed recent progress in 
the peace process and the steps taken toward the implementation 
of the Palestinian-Israeli Agreement, according to Minister 
al-Sharif. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

