<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Experts Said Preparing Sanaa's Air Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Experts Said Preparing Sanaa's Air Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1506092394 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 15 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM1506092394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russian Experts To Prepare Northern </F>
Air Force"] 
  [Text] London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Yemeni military 
sources have said that Russian aviation engineers have arrived 
in Sanaa recently to supervise the preparation of a squadron of 
Sukhoy fighter aircraft. 
  The information says that the five engineers who were 
granted 
entry visas to Yemen at Sanaa airport are: Alivov Aliksuvich, 
passport No. 1402266-41; Otsirnov Alikov Bigrovich, passport No. 
1402267-41; Blukhin Tsikhal Ikhliuvich, passport No. 1402265-41; 
Bgribineskiy Ginya Livovich, passport No. 1402264-41; Yamorin 
Vladimir Ivanovich, passport No. 1279750-431 [all names as 
transliterated]. 
  Aden had accused states it did not name of financing a huge 
arms deal which includes Sukhoy aircraft for Sanaa, saying that 
these arms are supplied from the former Soviet Union's arsenal 
in the Republic of Uzbekistan. 
  Information obtained by AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT says that Colonel 
Muhammad Salih al-Ahmar, half brother of the Yemeni president 
and commander of the Air Force and Air Defense, was behind the 
official invitation sent to the five Russian engineers, as 
mentioned in the original version of the invitation document 
sent by the General Staff in Sanaa. 
  Sources say that Yemeni Embassy officials in Moscow pointed 
out to the Russian experts that there was no means of transport 
to Sanaa as a result of the fighting, but the experts surprised 
Yemeni diplomats by saying they would go to Sanaa by a special 
plane -- which confirms the existence of direct contacts between 
Sanaa and the Russian experts without the Yemeni Embassy's 
knowledge. The sources add that northern military [officials] 
visit Tashkent to purchase various types of weapons, especially 
fighter aircraft. 

</TEXT>

