<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Velayati Informs Kohl German `Spy' Pardoned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Velayati Informs Kohl German `Spy' Pardoned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406185994 Tehran IRNA in English 1811 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 14, IRNA -- The Islamic Republic of 
Iran has pardoned German spy Helmut Szimkus, who had been 
arrested here in 1989. 
  Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati in his meeting with 
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in Bonn informed him of the pardon. 
  Szimkus had been condemned to death by a court after his 
trial. 
  German Chancellor Kohl and Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel had 
previously appealed for the Szimkus' release. 
  A diplomatic source said after the appeal, related 
authorities reviewed the case in light of the principled and 
realistic stances of the Bonn government vis-a-vis Iran, and 
Szimkus was eventually pardoned. 
  His pardon is expected to open a new chapter in Tehran-Bonn 
relations despite the impediments made by the U.S. and Britain. 

</TEXT>

