<H3> <TI>   Embassy: No IRGC Units Sent to Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Embassy: No IRGC Units Sent to Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406192894 Tehran IRNA in English 1916 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 14, IRNA -- The Iranian Embassy in 
Sanaa today categorically refuted as "false" a report by a 
french magazine that Iran had proposed to despatch units from 
the Islamic Revolution's Gurads Corps (IRGC) to Yemen. 
  Referring the recent 'LE POINT' allegations, the embassy 
said 
such unfounded reports and commentaries are printed in some 
Western papers with "quite clear objectives." 
  The embassy in its statement said Iran's clear stance 
concerning the current developments in the brotherly Republic of 
Yemen cannot be misportrayed through such propaganda. 
  The Islamic Republic of Iran supports a united Yemen, and 
hopes that present disputes would be settled peacefully, it said. 
  "National sovereignty and non-intervention in the internal 
affairs of Yemen should be respected in any solution," the 
statement said. 

</TEXT>

