<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Interior Minister Signs Security Protocol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Interior Minister Signs Security Protocol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1506092794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0230 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1506092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A protocol on security cooperation and border safety 
was signed yesterday by the interior ministers of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran and Turkey. On the basis of this protocol the 
two countries will increase their cooperation on the security of 
the two countries' borders, on confronting terrorism, and on 
fighting drug smuggling. 
  During the signing of this protocol, Besharati expressed 
satisfaction on the outcome of his discussions with Turkish 
officials and said that full agreement had been reached on all 
the topics discussed. 
  The Turkish interior minister referred to various Turkish 
officials' meetings with the Iranian delegation and stated that 
Besharati's visit to Turkey has solidified the two countries' 
friendly relations. 
  [Editor's note: In a similar report carried in its 0330 GMT 
newscast, Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First 
Program Network in Persian reports: "The Turkish interior 
minister has stated that no element acting against the Islamic 
Republic of Iran in Turkey will be allowed to remain on Turkish 
territory. The Turkish interior minister said that during his 
meeting with Besharati, he added that Turkish law-enforcement 
agents confront with sensitivity any act perpetrated against the 
Islamic Republic of Iran on Turkish territory."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

