<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Minister Supports Postponing OPEC Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Minister Supports Postponing OPEC Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406161594 Tehran IRNA in English 1501 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 14, IRNA -- OPEC should postpone its 
September meeting in a bid to boost the oil prices, Oil Minister 
Gholam Reza Aqazadeh said here Tuesday. 
  Referring to the OPEC oil ministers meeting in Vienna on 
Wednesday, Aqazadeh told the Persian daily ETTELA'AT that Iran 
would support every proposal which tended to help boost the 
prices. 
  He said the meeting has two important topics in its agenda, 
namely selection of the future secretary general of OPEC, and 
determination of the OPEC production ceiling. 
  On the former topic, he said there were two candidates from 
Iran and Venezuela for the post, and that from historical and 
qualitative points of view iran considered it its to be selected 
as the next OPEC secretary general. 
  Elsewhere, he said since Iran and Saudi Arabia produce half 
of the OPEC oil output, adoption of a joint stance by the two 
countries would certainly help OPEC to make a firm decision. 
  "Experience has shown that the two countries' agreement has 
had great impact on strengthening the prices," he noted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

