<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir Meets U.S. President's Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1406125594 Khartoum SUNA in English 0920 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1406125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 14 Jun (SUNA) -- President General 'Umar 
al-Bashir met Monday [13 June] at the General Command the 
visiting U.S. president's representative Melissa Wells and the 
accompanied delegation. The meeting reviewed the recent 
initiatives toward realizing peace in southern Sudan. General 
al-Bashir welcomed the representative's visit, stressing the 
government eagerness to solve the problem through the peaceful 
means, adding that the attempts for imposing sanctions has 
negatively affected the peace endeavors. 
  Wells in [a] statement following the meeting, described the 
visit as constructive, saying that she will leave for Wau to 
meet representatives of the other side (southerners). A message 
to General al-Bashir from Bill Clinton dealing with realization 
of peace in the south was conveyed by Mrs. Wells, Dr. Ghazi 
Salah al- Din, state minister, said. 

</TEXT>

