<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Briefs Council of Ministers on Kajo Kaji </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir Briefs Council of Ministers on Kajo Kaji </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1306210694 Khartoum SUNA in English 1630 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1306210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 12 Jun (SUNA) -- The Council of Ministers 
was briefed Sunday [12th June] by the president of the Republic, 
General 'Umar al-Bashir, on the details of recapturing of the 
strategic Kajo Kaji town by the Armed Forces. Al-Bashir has 
lauded zeal and struggle of the Armed Forces' troops and the 
People's Defense Forces' troops in the battle for restoring 
Kajo, explaining that the troops did not confront significant 
resistance from the outlaws who fled before the Army vanguards. 
  The president also pointed to the vast agricultural and 
economic potentialities of Kajo Kaji town. Adding that the 
government of Bahr al-Jabal State has finalized preparations for 
the return of Kajo Kaji citizens to their area. 
  Al-Bashir added that Bahr al-Jabal State is now totally free 
of outlaws, affirming that efforts to implement comprehensive 
development and to provide stability all over Bahr al-Jabal 
State will soon be started. He added that the federal 
government will extend every possible support to the services' 
utilities in Bahr al-Jabal State. 

</TEXT>

