<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Radio Will Not Transmit From Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Radio Will Not Transmit From Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1006171694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1530 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1006171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 10 Jun (MENA)--Muhammad Mu'tasim Hakim, 
spokesman for the Sudanese opposition Democratic Unionist Party 
[DUP], has denied newspaper reports that Sudanese opposition 
radio will transmit programs from Cairo. 
  In a statement to MENA, he said that Sudanese opposition has 
never thought of setting up a radio in Egypt or in any other 
Arab country to beam at Sudan. 
  He asserted that the Sudanese opposition is eager to improve 
relations between Egypt and Sudan and that opposition radio will 
transmit in the coming days from an undisclosed location. He 
explained that the transmission will be for two hours daily, one 
hour in the morning and one in the evening. He added that the 
broadcast will contain programs for the Sudanese people to 
uncover the Islamic front's plots in Sudan. 
  He said the radio will be called "The Opposition National 
Democratic Grouping Radio." He added that the grouping consists 
of the DUP led by Muhammad 'Uthman al-Mirghani, the Ummah Party, 
the Popular Movement led by Colonel John Garang, the southern 
parties, the Sudanese Communist Party, the Sudanese National 
Party, and 51 workers unions and federations, in addition to the 
Sudanese Army's legitimate command. 

</TEXT>

