<H3> <TI>   Armenian Foreign Minister Meets Officials, Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Foreign Minister Meets Officials, Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1406172394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 14 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1406172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Armenian Foreign Minister Vahan Papazyan continued 
his meetings with political officials. He met with Chamber of 
Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri and Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri; 
their talks dealt with bilateral relations. 
  Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz, who accompanied his Armenian 
counterpart to the Chamber of Deputies, said the decision to 
open a Lebanese embassy in Armenia was adopted by the government 
several months ago. He added that the final decision to name a 
Lebanese ambassador to Armenia is awaiting several 
administrative and fiscal arrangements. 
  Minister Papazyan left Beirut for Armenia at 1830 today. 
Before leaving Beirut Airport, he said that his visit was very 
good and that ties between the two countries will have legal 
[word indistinct]. He said discussions dealt with the 
possibility of operating a direct air route between Lebanon and 
Armenia. 

</TEXT>

