<H3> <TI>   King in `Good Health' After Checkup </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King in `Good Health' After Checkup </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1406203794 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 2006 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1406203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ladies and gentlemen: A short while ago, we learned 
that Lieutenant General Dr. Samir Farraj, the private physician 
of His Majesty King Husayn, has stated that his majesty the king 
left the Mayo Clinic medical center in Rochester in the United 
States this morning after undergoing extensive medical tests. 
The medical tests have shown that his majesty the king is 
enjoying good health, and that there are no traces of the 
disease which prompted surgery for his majesty the king two 
years ago. Consequently, such tests will be conducted once per 
year, instead of once every six months, Dr. Farraj added. 

</TEXT>

