<H3> <TI>   Weekly Urges Action Against U.S. Exercises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Weekly Urges Action Against U.S. Exercises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1406094894 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 13 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> JN1406094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ahmad al-Yamani] </F>
  [Text] Al-'Aqabah -- While preparations were under way to 
celebrate the anniversary of the Great Arab Revolt, led by 
al-Sharif Husayn I of Mecca, a large number of U.S. rapid 
intervention forces of aggression were present in the port city 
of al-'Aqabah and the al-Jafr area for their usual annual 
exercises and training on fighting us in the desert, sea, and 
air. 
  These forces had earlier participated in the 30-state 
aggression against Iraq and attacked our trucks and oil tankers, 
burning them and killing their occupants--our sons--while 
driving along the road in Jordan. 
  Allowing the U.S. forces of aggression to pursue training on 
fighting us or resting and recreating in Jordan requires all the 
national forces and their representatives in the House of 
Representatives to firmly prevent this provocation and stop 
these exercises, which are due to last one month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

